attributes.title: Apple Ipod Video 30GB Profit Distribution
attributes.description:
Created on February 24, 2010 by leo on Sourcemap.org:

A video iPod costs $299. Of this retail value, $162 is captured by American companies, $26 by Japan, $1 by Korea and $1 by Taiwan.  This is drawn from the New York Times article \"An iPod Has Global Value. Ask the (Many) Countries That Make It\"
